stories.title: Styris fined for dissent
stories.subTitle: India v New Zealand, Game 6, TVS Cup, Cuttack
stories.summary: Scott Styris, the Man of the Match in the one-day international against India at Cuttack, has been fined US$2500 for dissent

stories.title: The importance of the single
stories.subTitle: India v New Zealand, TVS Cup, Game 6, Cuttack
stories.summary: The ability to work the balls for singles won New Zealand the match

stories.title: Comfort zone bodes ill
stories.subTitle: India v New Zealand, TVS Cup, Game 6, Cuttack
stories.summary: In a way, the hysteria that followed the NatWest triumph, and the run to the World Cup final, symbolised everything that is rotten about Indian cricket, primarily our easily satiated appetite
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by Dileep Premachandran

stories.title: McMillan leads New Zealand to four-wicket win
stories.subTitle: India v New Zealand, Game 6, TVS Cup, Cuttack
stories.summary: Craig McMillan led the way with an unbeaten 82 as New Zealand beat India by four wickets to clinch their first win of the tournament
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Amit Varma
